@@TJvID3v1
<TITLEIMG TJvID3v1>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Multimedia.Audio
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Gives access to a file's ID3v1 tag.
Description
  Use the TJvID3v1 component to read, alter or remove the ID3v1 tag of a file.

  * To read a tag, set FileName to a name of a file, then set Active to true. \Now the   properties -
    such as Album, Artist - of the component give access to the fields of the ID3v1
    tag of the file.
  * If the file does not have an ID3v1 tag, then HasTag returns false.
  * After reading and setting these properties, you can call Commit to write the altered tag data to
    the file. If the file did not have a tag, one is created.
  * Alternatively, to remove a file's ID3v1 tag, set FileName to a name of file and call Erase. You
    don't have to set Active to true.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.Active
Summary
  Specifies whether or not the ID3v1 component is \open.
Description
  Use Active to determine or set whether the component is populated with data from the ID3v1 tag. When
  Active is false, the component cannot read or write data from or to the tag.

  When Active is set to true, the component reads the tag from the file specified by FileName.
See Also
  <LINK ReadID3v1Tag>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.Album
Summary
  Specifies the album where the MP3 comes from.
Description
  Use Album to specify the album where the MP3 comes from. Maximal length of the \string is 30.

  Before reading or setting Album, you must set Active to true.
See Also
  TJvID3v1.AlbumTrack, TJvID3v1.Artist, TJvID3v1.Comment, TJvID3v1.Genre, TJvID3v1.SongName,
  TJvID3v1.Year

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.AlbumTrack
Summary
  Specifies the tracknumber of the MP3.
Description
  Use AlbumTrack to specify the tracknumber of the MP3.

  In ID3v1.1, Michael Mutschler revised the specification of the comment field in order to implement
  the track number. The new length of the comment field is 28 character, thus making room to store a
  track number in the tag.

  If you specify a \string for Comment of length 29 or 30, AlbumTrack is ignored.

  Before reading or setting AlbumTrack, you must set Active to true.
See Also
  TJvID3v1.Album, TJvID3v1.Artist, TJvID3v1.Comment, TJvID3v1.Genre, TJvID3v1.SongName, TJvID3v1.Year

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.Artist
Summary
  Specifies the artist of the MP3
Description
  Use Artist to specify the artist of the MP3. Maximal length of the \string is 30.

  Before reading or setting Artist, you must set Active to true.
See Also
  TJvID3v1.Album, TJvID3v1.AlbumTrack, TJvID3v1.Comment, TJvID3v1.Genre, TJvID3v1.SongName,
  TJvID3v1.Year

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.Close
Summary
  Deactivates the component.
Description
  Call Close to set the Active property of the component to false. When Active is false, you can not
  change the tag of the file and all properties that specify fields of the ID3v1 tag are reset.
See Also
  TJvID3v1.Active, TJvID3v1.FileName, TJvID3v1.Open

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.Comment
Summary
  Specifies a comment for the MP3.
Description
  Use Comment to specify a comment for the MP3. Maximal length of the \string is 30.

  In ID3v1.1, Michael Mutschler revised the specification of the comment field in order to implement
  the track number. The new length of the comment field is 28 character, thus making room to store a
  track number in the tag.

  If you specify a \string for Comment of length 29 or 30, AlbumTrack is ignored.

  Before reading or setting Comment, you must set Active to true.
See Also
  TJvID3v1.Album, TJvID3v1.AlbumTrack, TJvID3v1.Artist, TJvID3v1.Genre, TJvID3v1.SongName,
  TJvID3v1.Year

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.Commit
Summary
  Writes the ID3v1 tag to the file.
Description
  Writes the data specified by the properties - such as Album, Artist - to the tag of the file
  specified by FileName. If the file does not have an ID3v1 tag, a tag is created.

  Active must have been set to true before calling Commit.
Return value
  Returns true if the commit was successful, otherwise returns false.
See Also
  <LINK WriteID3v1Tag>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.Erase
Summary
  Removes the ID3v1 tag.
Description
  Call Erase to remove the ID3v1 tag from the file specified by FileName. You don't have to set
  Active to true before you call Erase.
See Also
  <LINK RemoveID3v1Tag>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.FileName
Summary
  Specifies the file containing an ID3v1 tag.
Description
  FileName specifies the file:

  * From which the tag must be read when Active is set to true.
  * From which the tag will be altered if you call Commit.
  * From which the tag will be removed if you call Erase.
See Also
  TJvID3v1.Active, TJvID3v1.Close, TJvID3v1.Erase, TJvID3v1.HasTag, TJvID3v1.Open

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.Genre
Summary
  Specifies the offset of a genre in a <LINK TJvID3Genre_Table, predefined list>.
Description
  Use Genre to specify the offset of a genre. You can call <LINK ID3_Genres> to retrieve all valid
  genre strings.

  Before reading or setting Genre, you must set Active to true.
See Also
  <LINK ID3_Genres>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.GenreAsString
Summary
  Specifies the genre as \string for the MP3.
Description
  Use GenreAsString to specify a genre as \string for the MP3. The \string must be from the <LINK
  TJvID3Genre_Table, predefined list>.
  You can call <LINK ID3_Genres> to retrieve all valid genre strings.

  Before reading or setting GenreAsString, you must set Active to true.
See Also
  <LINK ID3_Genres>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.HasTag
Summary
  Indicates whether the MP3 file has an ID3v1 tag.
Description
  \Read HasTag to determine whether the MP3 file specified by FileName has an ID3v1 tag.
See Also
  <LINK HasID3v1Tag>

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.Open
Summary
  Activates the component.
Description
  Call Open to set the Active property for the component to true. When Active is true, you can change the tag by changing t
  e values of the properties of the component that represent fields of the tag such as Album, Artist
  - and then call Commit.

  When Active is set to true, the component reads the tag from the file specified by FileName.
See Also
  TJvID3v1.Active, TJvID3v1.Close, TJvID3v1.FileName, TJvID3v1.HasTag

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvID3v1.Refresh
Summary
  Rereads the ID3v1 tag.
Description
  Call Refresh to reread the tag from the file specified by FileName. Active must have been set to
  true before calling Refresh.
See Also
  TJvID3v1.Active, TJvID3v1.HasTag, TJvID3v1.Open

